d to date. The findings of the present study increase the number of helminth species parasitizing bats in Mexico.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Panti-May, Jes\u00fas Alonso", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hern\u00e1ndez-Mena, David Iv\u00e1n", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Torres-Castro, Marco Antonio", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Estrella-Mart\u00ednez, Erendira", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lugo-Caballero, C\u00e9sar", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Vidal-Mart\u00ednez, Victor M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hern\u00e1ndez-Betancourt, Silvia F.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/96c483ecc7603b27395c1d38154f0c31", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d1cb2df508809645277158f13884d618beb84faf99a71910a453fe9047b46bb5", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/758G7I8U", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/758G7I8U", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/f7551ab579a14d05edf950f3d82a6f80!/b39345-41818", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/26f7ce5dd404e33c6570edd4ba250d20", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"pages": "102302", "title": "Parasitology International", "volume": "82"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/96c483ecc7603b27395c1d38154f0c31"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zot